review_blob: pours a cloudy straw with a frothy head, herbal aroma, taste of tart wheat with hints of coriander and orange, overall a nice easy drinker, but maybe a little bland. disappointing as the white rabbit dark ale is one of my all time favorite beers.

pours a brilliant amber with a frothy white head, aroma of toffee and toast, flavor of toast, caramel and a sharp citrus bite.  overall a nice beer, had it as part of an aus/nz amber ale tasting night and it surprisingly ranked higher then some of the more well known brands.

dark ruby in the pour forming a nice frothy head 5/5 in appearance, sadly it goes down hill from there, sweet malty aroma and some alcohol, malt forward in the taste, caramel, toast, fruity esters and not enough hop presence.  a good beer but not great, was a little disappointed as i had heard some good things about the beer.

clear dark brown with a creamy off white head, aroma of burnt toffee, medium bodied with malty sweet toffee and chocolate, light on bitterness and carbonation. overall a nice beer to enjoy on a windy autumn day.

pours a cloudy orange with a big white head on it, a little light for the style, getting some herbal hops on the nose, taste is sweet and malty, a bit cloying with a lingering hop bitterness.  this beer is not for me
beer_name: Mildura Brewery Mallee Bull Strong Ale

review_blob: poured a brilliant gold with minimal head, slight sweet aroma, medium bitterness and a little bit sweet.  very boring beer, i got this in a boutique beer pack for valentines off the wife, firstly the fact that this beer is considered boutique scares me, the only thing premium about this ale is the name and the price, if i wanted a bland macro lager i could drink one the mega brands for a lot cheaper.
pours dark brown with a frothy off white head, roasted, toasted malt on the nose, surprisingly smooth in taste with definite toast, caramel and chocolate all working in harmony.  a nice beer

pours orange with a creamy white head, aroma of pine and floral hops, some nice toffee sweetness in the taste, nice sharp bitterness and i am getting lychee and pineapple in there too.  really enjoyed this one!

pours a clear dark amber with a nice frothy off white head, aroma of toffee and floral hops, taste is smooth and sweet toffee with a hint of chocolate and fruit, yet manages to  stay dry, crisp and refreshing. more complex then i was expecting, really love this beer!

pours bright gold with thick white head and vigorous carbonation. aroma of passionfruit soda (passiona), thin body, taste of passion/pinapple again (passiona), enjoyed this one very much, a great session beer

Poors orange gold with little head that quickly disapears, light carbonation in the english style nice malt toffee sweatness, finishing with sone resin hop biterness.  Slight toffee aroma, can not detect hops on the nose unusual for ipa.  Overall a decent drink, but wish it had more head and a nice hop aroma.

slightly sweet aroma, very light hazy color with a thick frothy head, champagne like carbonation, very light body, slight bitterness followed by a hint of honey, followed by the feeling of is that all a little underwhelming, would have liked more honey, but overall it would be the sort of drink i would like to enjoy at the football on a hot summers day.

great aroma of citrus and pine, pours clear golden straw with a lovely frothy bright white head, strong taste of fruity passionfruit/peach, with a kick of bitterness at the end, not enough sweetness and body to back it up.  overall feels like a lager trying to be a hoppy pale ale, and while i enjoyed the beer i would much rather have a pale ale to be honest.

the smell of this was amazing was like opening a bag of hops, and the taste was you guessed it very hoppy, stone fruit and citrus.  if you like hops then you will like this beer, had it on tap at the Popeye beer pub in Ryogoku, Tokyo and it was actually poured through cascade hop flowers off the tap.  i can only hope the bottle lives up to the on tap version as i dont want to fly all the way back to japan just to have this beer again.

Pours a hazy orange with frothy head, aroma is of bread, caramel and floral, taste is of fruity yeast with a nice refreshing bitterness backed by some sweet bread malt, medium bodied and soft carbonation. overall a nice quaffer perfect for drinking around the bbq on a hot summers day
pours golden with a white head (no surprise there), taste is sweet malt with some fruity hop presence, sweet fruity aroma. overall a nice beer on tap, a step up from the standard aussie lager.
beer_name: James Squire The Chancer Golden Ale

review_blob: pours pale hazy yellow with fluffy white head, aroma of coriander, taste has coriander and nuts and finishes bitter, slightly dry, overall a very drinkable beer.

pours golden with anfluffy white head, aroma of spice and vanilla, taste of subdued bread malt, vanilla and spice and definite farmhouse yeast.  overall a nice easy drinking interpretation of a belgian saison.

pours a bright copper color with a bright white head, taste has a little bit of malty sweetness, with some citrus and stone fruit, aroma is cascade floral citrus. a bit like a subdued version of Little Creatures Pale Ale, still very drinkable and very session-able, a nice introduction for those looking for an alternative to standard aussie lagers.

pours a nice clear brown color with off white head, taste is caramel, chocolate, grapefruit and blackberry and english yeast fruitiness. get cascade hops in the aroma as well as chocolate.  very complex yet balanced brown ale, slightly lighter in body then most interpretations of the style which helps with its drinkability in the aussie heat.

nice golden brown color with a white long lasting head, tastes of caramel and nutty malt with some nice floral and citrus hop flavor and aroma.  overall a good beer, but slightly over hoped for the light body of the beer.

taste is caramel and citrus and a nice clean bitterness, very balanced, nice floral citrus aroma, pours a pale orange with a nice white head.  overall a very balanced beer. the best beer i tried while traveling in the states.

taste is caramel, citrus and finishing with stone fruit all very balanced with a definite cascade hop aroma and lovely copper color with an off white head.  an almost perfect interpretation of the style and the best pale ale in Australia in my opinion.
